SUMMARY:Cider Run 2026
DESCRIPTION:The ISRA Cider Run is an annual automotive hobbyist event hosted by the Indiana Street Rod Association at the Brown County 4H Fairgrounds in Nashville, Indiana. Since 1972, this gathering brings together street rod and classic car enthusiasts — members and non-members alike — for a day of cruising, car displays, camaraderie, and community fun. Open to all makes and models, the Cider Run offers a relaxed atmosphere to connect with fellow motorsports fans, enjoy scenic Brown County, and celebrate automotive passion each September.\n
